    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-07-17T19:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-07-17T19:36:00-05:00" n="189"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d189">
                <head>189. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Jordan</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d189fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 785.00/7–1658. Top Secret; <gloss target="#t_Niact1">Niact</gloss>.
                        Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_RSW1">Rockwell</persName> and cleared by
                            <persName corresp="#p_RWM1">Rountree</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_RGF1">Reinhardt</persName>. Repeated to London, Paris, and
                            <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-07-17T20:36:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1958—8:36 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>159. Embtel 132.<note n="2" xml:id="d189fn2">
                        <ref target="#d181">Document 181</ref>.</note> Please inform Hussein in
                    response to his request for US military intervention that US immediately upon
                    receipt request consulted with <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> at highest
                    level. <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> has already responded by dispatch of
                    troops and US has indicated its full support for this <pb facs="0354" n="322"
                        xml:id="pg_322"/> action by flying military planes over Jordan this morning
                    and statement of strong support issued today.<note n="3" xml:id="d189fn3">See
                            <ref target="#d186">Document 186</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>We trust these actions will give the necessary support to His Majesty in his
                    courageous and forthright efforts to maintain the independence and integrity of
                        <gloss target="#t_HKJ1">HKJ</gloss>. We will continue to keep the situation
                    under closest observation to determine whether further measures are
                    necessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
